{#- LLM-facing text is English-only: Cyrillic uses roughly 2–3× more tokens per word.
    This Jinja comment is stripped and never sent to the model.
    docs/ARCHITECTURE.md §6.2: tool-spec for route `cli_intent`. -#}
{
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "cli_intent",
    "description": "Tool-only: call once; no assistant text outside tool_calls. Maze move — EXPLORE the file/system part of the labyrinth. Request shell execution on the agent host. Default: sandbox (read-only OS, user scope). Set privileged: true for system-scope commands (writes outside sandbox, package install, systemctl as root); on most hosts that triggers HITL confirmation (unless disabled in threlium.yaml). Shell chains allowed: use &&, ;, or | in argv or [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"…\"]. Safety: non-interactive flags; limit output; no secrets in argv.\n\nWhen NOT to use: a fact retrievable from the knowledge graph → memory_query first; broad multi-step repo survey → subagent_intent with an inventory-only task.\n\nargv[0] is an OS binary (ls, cat, rg, find, head, git, python3, …), NEVER the name of an FSM route. Routes — memory_query, reflect, formal_reason, response_append, response_edit, response_observe, response_finalize, thread_memory, global_memory, subagent_intent, tasks_upsert — are separate tools. A cli_intent whose argv[0] is a route name is bounced back as an observation; call the real tool instead.\n\nDiscovery examples: [\"rg\", \"-l\", \"EmailBridge\", \"path\"], [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"rg -l Foo path | head -n 20\"]. Privileged example: [\"apt-get\", \"install\", \"-y\", \"pkg\"] with privileged: true.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "argv": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {"type": "string", "minLength": 1, "maxLength": 4000},
          "minItems": 1,
          "maxItems": 64,
          "description": "Command and arguments as argv array; use separate tokens for shell operators (&&, |, ;). For a full shell line use [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"…\"]. argv[0] is the binary name for simple commands."
        },
        "cwd": {
          "type": "string",
          "maxLength": 4000,
          "description": "Working directory for execution (optional)."
        },
        "privileged": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "description": "If true, run in system scope (uid=0) after HITL when enabled on this host. Default false = sandbox."
        },
        "reasoning": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 2000,
          "description": "Why this command is needed — short text for logs and HITL confirmation."
        }
      },
      "required": ["argv", "reasoning"],
      "additionalProperties": false
    }
  }
}
